{{Flag entry|Image=Proposed Ensign of Qing Navy 1863.svg|Width=200 |Caption=Proposed Naval Ensign by Horatio Nelson Lay}}
{{End flag gallery}}

;Beiyang Fleet (1874-1890)

The Beiyang Fleet was created in 1874, and several rank flags were introduced based on the traditional five color officials' flags of the old Chinese navy.
{{Begin flag gallery}}
{{Flag entry|Image=Flag of Fleet Commander of the Beiyang Fleet.svg|Width=200 |Caption=Admiral's Flag}}
{{Flag entry|Image=Flag of Deputy Commanders of the Beiyang Fleet.svg|Width=200 |Caption=Deputy Commanders's Flag}}
{{Flag entry|Image=Flag of High-ranking Official of Beiyang Fleet.svg|Width=200 |Caption=High-ranking Official's Flag, for officials other than navy}}
{{End flag gallery}}

;Beiyang Navy (1890-1909)

The Beiyang Fleet became the national navy by ''Regulations of the Beiyang Fleet'' in 1888. However rank flags were not updated until 1890, when William Metcalfe Lang and [[Liu Buchan]] disputed about their rank flags in an [[Liu Buchan#Life|incident]]. Therefore, the [[British Royal Navy]] advisers proposed five new rank flags to replace the simple two rank flags system.<ref>Drawings of the flags in use at the present time by various nations, Royal Navy Admiral</ref>
{{Begin flag gallery}}
{{Flag entry|Image=Imperial Chinese Navy Admiral's Flag (1905-1909).svg|Width=200 |Caption=Proposed Admiral's Flag}}
{{Flag entry|Image=Imperial Chinese Navy Fleet Commander's Flag (1905-1909).svg|Width=200 |Caption=Proposed Vice Admiral's Flag}}
{{Flag entry|Image=Imperial Chinese Navy Squadron Commander's Flag (1905-1909).svg|Width=200 |Caption=Proposed Rear Admiral's Flag}}
{{Flag entry|Image=Imperial Chinese Navy Commodore's Flag (1905-1909).svg|Width=200 |Caption=Proposed Commodore 1st Class's Flag}}
{{Flag entry|Image=Proposed Imperial Chinese Navy 2nd Commodore's Flag (1890).svg|Width=200 |Caption=Proposed Commodore 2nd Class's Flag}}
{{End flag gallery}}

However these proposals were not adopted by the Qing dynasty.<ref>Images of Chinese Naval Ships(1855-1911) / 中国军舰图志(1855-1911)" by Chen Rui 陈悦, {{ISBN|9787545811544}}</ref> New rank flags were introduced later in 1890.<ref>{{lang|ja|清国北洋海軍実況一班}}</ref>
{{Begin flag gallery}}
{{Flag entry|Image=Flag of the Admiral of the Beiyang Fleet.svg|Width=200 |Caption=Admiral's Flag}}
{{Flag entry|Image=Flag of Provincial Commander-in-Chief of Beiyang Fleet.svg|Width=200 |Caption=High-ranking Official's Flag}}
{{Flag entry|Image=Flag of the Commander of Minelayers of Beiyang Fleet (1890-1909).svg|Width=200 |Caption=Commander of Torpedo Boat's Flag}}
{{Flag entry|Image=Flag of Commodore of Beiyang Fleet (1890-1909).svg|Width=200 |Caption=Commodore's Flag}}
{{End flag gallery}}

;Imperial Navy (1909-1911)

After the total defeat of the Beiyang Navy in [[First Sino-Japanese War]] in 1894, the new imperial navy was reorganized following the establishment of the department of navy in 1909.
[[Imperial Chinese Navy]] adopted the national flag in the canton of naval flags in 1909.<ref name=qingnavy>Source: [http://www.dpm.org.cn/shtml/117/@/7744.html 北京故宮《海軍旗式及章服圖說》] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140109074616/http://www.dpm.org.cn/shtml/117/%40/7744.html |date=2014-01-09 }} ("Illustration of Naval flags and Uniforms", Palace Museum, Beijing, China)</ref>
{{Begin flag gallery}}
{{Flag entry|Image=Imperial Chinese Navy Secretary's Flag (1909-1911).svg|Width=200 |Caption=Secretary's Flag}}
{{Flag entry|Image=Imperial Chinese Navy Admiral's Flag (1909-1911).svg|Width=200 |Caption=Admiral's Flag}}
{{Flag entry|Image=Imperial Chinese Navy Vice Admiral's Flag (1909-1911).svg|Width=200 |Caption=Vice Admiral's Flag}}
{{Flag entry|Image=Imperial Chinese Navy Rear Admiral's Flag (1909-1911).svg|Width=200 |Caption=Rear Admiral's Flag}}
{{End flag gallery}}
{{Begin flag gallery}}
{{Flag entry|Image=Imperial Chinese Navy Senior Officer's Flag (1909-1911).svg|Width=200 |Caption=Senior Officer's Flag}}
{{Flag entry|Image=Imperial Chinese Navy Fleet Leader's Flag (1909-1911).svg|Width=200 |Caption=Fleet Leader's Flag}}
{{End flag gallery}}

==Flags based on Qing dynasty flag==
;Chinese Eastern Railway
[[Chinese Eastern Railway#Flags|Flag]] of [[Chinese Eastern Railway]] adopted a combination of Qing dynasty and Russian flags. The flag was not updated until 1915.<ref>[http://www.crwflags.com/fotw/flags/cn-cer.html Chinese Eastern Railway Company (China)]</ref>
