'''Zaguan''' refers to a house plan configuration where a central passageway leads from a front door to a patio or a courtyard. This is found in historic houses in Mexico and in the southwestern U.S.<ref>[http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/zaguan]</ref>
[[File:O%27Keeffe_Home3.jpg|right|thumb|Zaguan at [[Georgia O'Keeffe Home and Studio|Georgia O'Keeffe House]]]] An example is the [[Ortiz House (Yuma, Arizona)|Ortiz House]] in [[Yuma, Arizona]]. Another is the [[Georgia O'Keeffe Home and Studio]] in New Mexico.
